  "prompt": "Why are upload speeds to Gmail so slow for attachments?",
  "response": "There are several potential reasons for slow Gmail attachment uploads:\n\n1. File size\n- Large files naturally take longer to upload\n- Gmail has upload size limits (typically 25MB)\n\n2. Internet connection\n- Slow or unstable internet speeds can significantly impact upload times\n- Upload speeds are often slower than download speeds\n\n3. Server congestion\n- Gmail's servers might be experiencing high traffic\n- Peak usage times can slow upload speeds\n\n4. Network infrastructure\n- Your local network or internet service provider might have bandwidth limitations\n\n5. Computer performance\n- Older or slower computers can process uploads more slowly\n\nTo improve upload speeds, you can:\n- Use a faster internet connection\n- Upload during off-peak hours\n- Compress large files before uploading\n- Use Google Drive for larger files\n- Check your computer's performance and network settings",
